The deferred write introduced by https://github.com/nodejs/node/pull/61800 wraps the write operation in `queueMicrotask()`. A race condition exists where the pipe can shutdown and release the writer between when `[kChunk]` schedules the microtask and when it executes, causing an `ERR_INTERNAL_ASSERTION` because `writer[[stream]]` is undefined.

Fix by checking `writer[kState].stream === undefined` in the deferred microtask before attempting the write. This condition is only true after `finalize()` has released the writer, precisely targeting the crash without interfering with the spec requirement that already-read chunks are written to a still-writable destination during shutdown.

Fixes: https://github.com/nodejs/node/issues/63732
